{"lemma":"خَراجٌ","slug":"خَراجٌ","root":"خ.ر.ج","root_slug":"خ-ر-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ر-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَراج","root":"خرج","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10284","n10285","n10290"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"public levy, subsidy; poll-tax, tribute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"abscess, boil, aposteme"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From خ ر ج (ḵ r j) in the sense “to extract” or “take out”, with phono-semantic matching from Middle Persian apparently in an unattested by-form of by-itself Iranian-origin 𐫍𐫡𐫃 (hrg /⁠harg⁠/), 𐫟𐫡𐫃 (xrg /⁠xarg⁠/), 𐫆𐫡𐫵𐫃 (hrːg /⁠harg⁠/, “tribute”) surfacing as Old Armenian հարկ (hark) etc., an already Old Persian contamination *harākah (“tribute, tax, any public charge based on land property”) on the model of Imperial Aramaic 𐡄𐡋𐡊𐡀 (hlkʾ /⁠hălāḵā⁠/, “tribute, tax, any public charge based on land property”), itself calqued from Akkadian 𒅋𒆪 (il-ku /⁠ilku⁠/, “corvée, tribute, any public charge based on land property”). Also attested several times in Biblical Aramaic הֲלָכָא (/⁠hălāḵā⁠/) but otherwise missing in Aramaic."},"ipa":["/xa.raːd͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10284","headword_ar":"خَرَاجٌ","root":"xrj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarojN","text_ar":"خَرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) both also written with damm, [i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuraAjN","text_ar":"خُرَاجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xurojN","text_ar":"خُرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (K,) but the former mode of writing them is that which more commonly obtains, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_itaAwapN","text_ar":"اـِتَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tax,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribute, which is taken from the property of people; an impost,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain amount of the property of people, which is given forth yearly; a tax upon lands &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revenue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gain, derived from land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and then applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land-tax, which is taken by the Sultán:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poll-tax paid by the free non-Muslim subjects of a Muslim government:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjN","text_ar":"خَرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies especially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a land-tax:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarojN","text_ar":"خَرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a poll-tax:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar:) or the former also signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poll-tax paid by the free non-Muslim subjects of a Muslim government:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is a term which was applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a yearly land-tax which 'Omar imposed upon the people of the Sawád"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of El-'Irák"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: then, to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"landtax which the people of a land taken by convention agreed to pay;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and their lands were termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjiy~apN","text_ar":"خَرَاجِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to Bd, it is a name for the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proceeds of land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and has then been used to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profits arising from possessions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revenue derived from the increase of lands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from slaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"animals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Er-Ráfi'ee, its primary signification is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an impost which the master requires to be paid him by his slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Zj, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarojN","text_ar":"خَرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an [obsolete] inf. n.: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjN","text_ar":"خَرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a name for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which comes forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and he also explains the latter word by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faYo'N","text_ar":"فَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarojN","text_ar":"خَرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DariybapN","text_ar":"ضَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizoyapN","text_ar":"جِزْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjN","text_ar":"خَرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", L, TA) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoraAjN","text_ar":"اَخْرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axaAriyju","text_ar":"اَخَارِيجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. pl.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axorijapN","text_ar":"اَخْرِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaraAju biAlD~amaAni","text_ar":"الخَرَاجُ بِالضَّمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a saying ascribed to Mohammad, (K, TA,) occurring in a trad. of 'Áïsheh, of disputed authority, but affirmed by several authors to be genuine, means, accord. to most of the lawyers, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The revenue"},{"kind":"text","text":"derived from the slave"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is"},{"kind":"text","text":"the property of the purchaser"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because of the responsibility"},{"kind":"text","text":"which he has borne for him: (A, * Mgh, * K, TA:) for one purchases a slave, and imposes upon him the task of producing a revenue for a time, and then may discover in him a fault which the seller had concealed; wherefore he has a right to return him and to receive back the price; but the revenue which he had required the slave to produce is his lawful property, because he had been responsible for him; and if he had perished, part of his property had perished: (K, * TA:) in a similar manner IAth explains it, as relating to a male or female slave or to other property. (TA.) ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarojN","text_ar":"خَرْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjN","text_ar":"خَرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as used in the Kur xxiii. 74 mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reward."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr.) Some, for ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarojFA","text_ar":"خَرْجًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in this instance, read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjFA","text_ar":"خَرَاجًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjN","text_ar":"خَرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The taste"},{"kind":"text","text":"of fruit; this being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xrAj","text_ar":"خراج"},{"kind":"text","text":"of lands &c. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyjN","text_ar":"خَرِيجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n10285","headword_ar":"خُرَاجٌ","root":"xrj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pimples,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small swellings"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pustules:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a coll. gen. n.:] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) or [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of pustule termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dum~al","text_ar":"دُمَّل"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, that come forth upon the body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purulent pustules,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imposthumes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that come forth upon the body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spontaneous swelling that comes forth upon the body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ulcerous swelling that comes forth upon a beast of the equine kind and upon other animals:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axorijapN","text_ar":"اَخْرِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xirojaAnN","text_ar":"خِرْجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraAjN","text_ar":"خَرَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n10290","headword_ar":"خَرَّاجٌ","root":"xrj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaArijN","text_ar":"خَارِجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xurajapN","text_ar":"خُرَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}